{{!--
  Event Prompt Template for Code Platforms

  This template is designed for code repository platforms (GitHub, Linear)
  where the workflow involves creating/updating code via branches, PRs, and commits.

  For conversational platforms (Slack), use event-prompt-slack.hbs instead.

  ─── Available Template Variables ───────────────────────────────────────────────

  Top-level:
    {{id}}                  Full event identifier (e.g. "github:owner/repo:opened:123:uuid")
    {{provider}}            Provider name: "github" | "linear"
    {{type}}                Event type: "issue" | "pull_request" (GitHub) | "issue" (Linear)
    {{action}}              Action that triggered the event (e.g. "opened", "closed", "edited", "poll")

  resource.*:
    {{resource.number}}     Issue or PR/MR number (e.g. 123)
    {{resource.title}}      Title / summary
    {{resource.description}} Body / description
    {{resource.url}}        URL to the issue or PR/MR
    {{resource.state}}      Current state (e.g. "open", "closed")
    {{resource.repository}} GitHub: repository full name (e.g. "owner/repo")
                            Linear: team key (e.g. "ENG")
    {{resource.author}}     GitHub: login username of the original issue/PR author
                            Linear: display name of the original creator (e.g. "Jane Doe")
                            Used as git co-author on commits — always the original creator,
                            regardless of who triggered this event
    {{resource.assignees}}  Array of assignees (truthy if any assignees exist)
    {{resource.labels}}     Array of label/tag name strings (optional)
    {{resource.branch}}     Head branch name — GitHub PRs only (optional)
    {{resource.mergeTo}}    Target branch — GitHub PRs only (optional)

  resource.comment.* (only present when event is triggered by a comment):
    {{resource.comment.body}}   Comment text
    {{resource.comment.author}} Comment author username
    {{resource.comment.url}}    Direct URL to the comment (optional; not always provided)

  actor.*:
    {{actor.username}}      Username (or display name for Linear) of whoever triggered the event
    {{actor.id}}            Provider-specific actor ID

  metadata.*:
    {{metadata.timestamp}}  ISO 8601 timestamp of the event
    {{metadata.deliveryId}} Webhook delivery ID — GitHub webhooks only
    {{metadata.polled}}     true if received via polling; absent for webhooks

  ─── Built-in Helpers ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

    {{resourceLink}}        Formatted link to the issue/PR (uses resource.url + resource.number)
    {{commentLink}}         Formatted link to the comment (uses resource.comment.url)
    {{#eq a b}}...{{/eq}}  Renders block if a === b
    {{#ne a b}}...{{/ne}}  Renders block if a !== b
    {{#and a b}}...{{/and}} Renders block if both a and b are truthy
    {{#or a b}}...{{/or}}  Renders block if either a or b is truthy
    {{link text url provider}} Renders a formatted hyperlink

  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
--}}
